Task Manager CLI
A lightweight command-line task management application built in Python. Manage your tasks directly from the terminal — no internet connection or external services required.

Features
•	Create tasks with titles, descriptions, priorities and due dates
•	Filter tasks by status: todo, in_progress, review, done
•	Automatic priority scoring based on urgency and due dates
•	Tag tasks with custom labels like blocker or critical
•	Track overdue tasks at a glance
•	View task statistics and weekly completion trends

Requirements
•	Python 3.8 or higher
•	No external libraries required — uses Python built-ins only

Installation
1.	Clone the repository:
git clone https://github.com/wethinkcode/ai-code-exercises.git
2.	Navigate to the TaskManager folder:
cd ai-code-exercises/use-cases/code-algorithms/python/TaskManager
3.	Verify Python is installed:
python --version
That's it — no pip install needed!

Quick Start
# Create your first task
python cli.py create "Buy groceries" -p 2 -u 2026-06-20

# List all tasks
python cli.py list

# Mark a task as done
python cli.py status <task_id> done

# View statistics
python cli.py stats

